A man has been killed and five others injured during house fire on Hamilton Road, Rustenburg late last night.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said: &#8220;The body of the man was found lying inside one of the rooms. Sadly, the man had already succumbed to his multiple injuries and there was nothing that the paramedics could do for him, he was than declared dead.&#8221;When paramedics arrived at the scene, The fire had already being extinguished.Two from the five patients who sustained injuries were in a critical condition after paramedics found that they have sustained burn wounds on their bodies. The three other had sustained moderate burn wounds.Advanced life support interventions were provided to the critically injured patients.The cause of the fire is unknown but relevant services are investigating the incident.-TNA Reporter 